decision_conditions:
Condition : 11 - Before the development is first occupied:
The three planting beds  indicated in green on the approved forecourt layout shall be planted with low growing evergreen shrubs to provide complete ground cover and any plants that die or are removed in the first five years after they are planted shall be replaced with comparable specimens in the next available planting season after their removal or death;
The proposed dwarf wall on the street boundary shall be constructed from a point adjacent to the westernmost corner of the approved new house to the boundary with the front garden of 69 Park Road and in a form matching the front garden wall of 69 Park Road.  The rest of the boundary shall be enclosed by a two-metre high close-boarded fence/brick wall or the existing side and rear boundary treatment shall be retained;
The forecourt shall be laid in porous materials that shall first have been submitted to and approved by the local planning authority under Condition 6 of this permission
